ws/uk-england-hampshire-25760383|title=Bone fragment 'could be King Alfred or son Edward'|work=BBC News}}\n* {{cite news|ref={{SfnRef|Bristol University|2010}}|date=17 June 2010|url=http://www.bristol.ac.uk/news/2010/7073.html|title=Bones confirmed as those of Saxon Princess Eadgyth|publisher=[[Bristol University]]}}\n* {{citation|mode=cs1|ref=harv|last=Bradshaw|first=Anthony|year=1999|title=The Burghal Hidage: Alfred's Towns|url=http://www.ogdoad.force9.co.uk/alfred/alfhidage.htm}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Brooks|first=Nicholas|year=1984|title=The Early History of the Church of Canterbury: Christ Church from 597 to 1066|pages=172\u201373}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Brooks|first=N.P.|last2=Graham-Campbell|first2=J.A.|author-link2=James Graham-Campbell|year=1986|chapter=Reflections on the Viking-age silver hoard from Croydon, Surrey|title=Anglo-Saxon Monetary History: Essays in Memory of Michael Dolley|pages=91\u2013110}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Cannon|first=John|year=1997|title=The Oxford Companion to British History|publisher=Oxford University Press|location=Oxford|isbn=0-19-866176-2|url=https://archive.org/details/oxfordcompaniont00john_0}}\n* {{cite book|ref=harv|last=Cornwell |first=Bernard|year=2009|title=The Burning Land|url=https://archive.org/details/burningland00corn|url-access=registration|publisher=Harper}}\n* {{cite web|ref={{SfnRef|The Church Monuments Society|2014}}|date=29 January 2014|title=The Post-Mortem Adventures Of Alfred The Great|website=The Church Monuments Society|url=http://www.churchmonumentssociety.org/Alfred.html|accessdate=7 February 2016}}\n* {{cite web|ref=harv|last=Cohen|first=Tamara|date=27 March 2013|url=https://www.iol.co.za/news/could-these-be-the-bones-of-alfred-the-great-1492441|title=Could these be the bones of Alfred the Great?|publisher=IOL Scitech|accessdate=3 October 2017}}\n* {{cite web|ref=harv|year=2011|url=https://www.royal.uk/alfred-great-r-871-899|title=HomeHistory of the Monarchy: English Monarchs (400 A