whether the subject is actually notable. If so, please consider writing an article yourself. Those without a Wikipedia article are removed after one month.\n\n(2) Please understand that the intent of this article is to report notable deaths. Tragic deaths, while unfortunate, do not necessarily render the deceased \"notable\". If you report the death of a subject that does not already have a Wikipedia article, please consider starting one, provided that the deceased is notable. Please include third-party sources other than the obituary.\n\n(3) Please add entries in alphabetical order by family name. Please avoid overlinking. As such, please do not add links to nationalities, common occupations, or common causes of death. Rather, please include only \"links that aid navigation and understanding\". Thank you.\n\n(4) References should be in <ref>[url & title]</ref> format, as full citations make the page too slow to load, and too big to edit.\n\n* * * * * * * Please adhere to the guidelines above when adding a name to this article * * * * * * *\n\n--->\n\n==March 2002==\n\n===1===\n*[[John Blume]], 92, American [[structural engineer]], known as \"the father of earthquake engineering\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.stanford.edu/news/2002/march13/blumeobit-313.html|last=Shwartz|first=Mark|title=John Blume, 'father of earthquake engineering,' dies|work=[[Stanford University]]|date=2002-03-13|accessdate=2019-03-16}}</ref>\n*[[C. Farris Bryant]], 87, American Governor ([[List of Governors of Florida|34th Governor of Florida]] from 1961 to 1965).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/06/nyregion/c-farris-bryant-87-governor-of-florida-at-turning-point.html|last=Lavietes|first=Stuart|title=C. Farris Bryant, 87, Governor Of Florida at Turning Point|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=2002-03-06|accessdate=2019-02-26}}</ref>\n*[[Dino Casanova]], 35, American professional wrestler, heart attack.\n*[[John Challens]], 86, British scientist and civil servant, helped develop Britain's first atomic bomb.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2002/mar/12/guardianobituaries.physicalsciences|last=Wright|first=Pearce|title=John Challens|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2002-03-12|accessdate=2019-02-26}}</ref>\n*[[Barbara Davies]], 46, English teacher and peace campaigner ([[Christian CND|Christian Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2002/mar/09/guardianobituaries.nuclear|last=Flessati|first=Valerie|title=Barbara Eggleston|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2002-03-08|accessdate=2019-04-04}}</ref>\n*[[Marion Flanagan]], 77, American football player.\n*[[David Mann (songwriter)|David Mann]], 85, American songwriter.\n*[[Henry H. \"Hank\" Price]], 86, American politician.\n*[[Bob Smith (defensive back, born 1925)|Bob Smith]], 76, American professional football player ([[Brooklyn Dodgers (AAFC)|Brooklyn Dodgers]], [[Detroit Lions]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/S/SmitBo02.htm|title=Bob Smith|work=[[Pro-Football-Reference.com]]|accessdate=2019-02-26}}</ref>\n*[[Hocine Soltani]], 29, Algerian boxer, murdered.\n*[[Doreen Waddell]], 36, British soul singer ([[Soul II Soul]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/1386785/Soul-star-who-was-shoplifter-dies-as-she-flees-from-store.html|last=Payne|first=Stewart|title=Soul star who was shoplifter dies as she flees from store|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=2002-03-05|accessdate=2019-04-28}}</ref>\n*[[Roger Plumpton Wilson]], 96, British Anglican prelate.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/news/2002/mar/04/guardianobituaries.religion|last=De-la-Noy|first=Michael|title=The Rt Rev Roger Wilson|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=2002-03-03|accessdate=2019-05-02}}</ref>\n\n===2===\n*[[Andr\u00e9s Archila]], 88, Guatemalan violinist and music conductor.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.encyclopedia.com/humanities/encyclopedias-almanacs-transcripts-and-maps/archila-andres-1913-2002|title=Archila, Andr\u00e9s (1913\u20132002)|work=[[Encyclopedia.com]]|accessdate=2019-03-11}}</ref>\n*[[Jeanne Burbank]], 86, American scientist in the field of electrochemistry.\n*[[Alvin Eicoff]], 80, American advertising executive, widely recognized as a founder of [[direct response television]] advertising.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2002/03/09/business/alvin-eicoff-innovator-in-late-night-tv-ads-dies-at-80.html|last=Lavietes|first=Stuart|title=Alvin Eicoff, Innovator in Late-Night TV Ads, Dies at 80|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=2002-03-09|accessdate=2019-04-08}}</ref>\n*[[Friedrich Gorenstein]], 69, Russian-Jewish author and screenwriter.\n*[[Don Haig]], 68, Canadian filmmaker, editor, and producer.\n*[[Ellis L. Perry]], 82, American vice admiral.\n*[[Fritz-Rudolf Schultz]], 85, German World War II army officer and politician.\n*[[Alexei Yegorov (ice hockey, born 1975)|Alexei Yegorov]], 26, Russian professional ice hockey player ([[San Jose Sharks]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hockey-reference.com/players/y/yegoral01.html|title=Alexei Yegorov|work=Hockey-Reference.com. [[Sports Reference]]|accessdate=2019-04-22}}</ref>\n\n===3===\n*[[Henry Nathaniel Andrews]], 91, American [[paleobotanist]], recognized as an expert on the [[Devonian]] and [[Carboniferous]] periods.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nasonline.org/publications/biographical-memoirs/memoir-pdfs/andrews-henry-n-jr.pdf|last=Phillips|first=Tom L.|title=HENRY NATHANIEL ANDREWS, JR.June 15, 1910\u2014March 3, 2002|work=[[National Academy of Sciences]]|accessdate=2019-03-11}}</ref>\n*[[G. M. C. Balayogi]], 50, Indian lawyer and politician.\n*[[Calvin Carri\u00e8re]], 80, American fiddler.\n*[[Marvin E. Frankel]], 81, American judge ([[United States federal judge|United States District Judge]] of the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of New York]]).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.fjc.gov/node/1380896|title=Frankel, Marvin E.|work=[[Federal Judicia